00:50:31.810 --> 00:50:36.150
&gt;&gt; You mentioned that the
servers have data on the speed

00:50:36.150 --> 00:50:40.200
on which they're recorded,
how often do you find that,

00:50:40.200 --> 00:50:43.270 position:56%
do you see much variation-- i.e. the
original recording [inaudible] was

00:50:43.270 --> 00:50:44.570
spring loaded?

00:50:44.570 --> 00:50:48.820
Do you see variations or like decay

00:50:48.820 --> 00:50:53.230
in the [inaudible]
speed in the cylinder?

00:50:53.230 --> 00:50:56.630
&gt;&gt; Olivia Dill: So the question
was about the accuracy of the RP--

00:50:56.630 --> 00:51:00.000
of the speed data that we have and
any variations that we've seen.

00:51:00.000 --> 00:51:03.390
So there's two kind
of pieces to that.

00:51:03.390 --> 00:51:07.610
We get our data from-- there was
a massive survey of the collection

00:51:07.610 --> 00:51:12.040 position:56%
that was done a while ago by Richard
