to the surface of the cylinder

01:03:11.200 --> 01:03:14.350
which is, from a preservation
standard,

01:03:14.350 --> 01:03:20.570
not desirable because that's
more degradation on the surface.

01:03:20.570 --> 01:03:27.910
So, yes it is possible to go higher
than that sort of 4000 cutoff,

01:03:27.910 --> 01:03:31.010
but again, at the risk of
damaging your cylinder surface.

01:03:31.010 --> 01:03:36.920
And we did do some studies over
the summer to see exactly what

01:03:36.920 --> 01:03:43.140
that tradeoff is but we have
yet to really assess that out.

